media:group.media:description:

entry.title: Ultimate Controller Comparison | Input lag, etc. (PS5, PS4, Xbox SX/Elite 2/One, eSwap Pro)

media:group.media:title: Ultimate Controller Comparison | Input lag, etc. (PS5, PS4, Xbox SX/Elite 2/One, eSwap Pro)
media:group.media:description:
This video is a reupload because of a bug that influenced the input lag data of the PlayStation controllers. Make sure to check it out, to see what has changed. Here is a detailed explanation of the issue: https://youtu.be/82K3Pb0178g.
Today, I bring you all the next-gen, premium, and last-gen controller information on the DualSense, Xbox Series X controller, Xbox Elite Series 2, Thrustmaster eSwap Pro, DualShock 4 and Xbox One S controller that you could ever ask for. Input lag; polling rates; data on stick tension, accuracy, sensitivities, and deadzones; button forces; trigger travel; controller weight; and a lot more.
The software that shows as Precision Tester can be found as JoyTester2.exe online. I don't think there is an official download anywhere so use at your own risk.

entry.title: Does input lag matter? A RL experiment

media:group.media:title: Does input lag matter? A RL experiment
media:group.media:description:
Experiment updates: https://experiment.rocketscience.fyi
Input lag is a topic I've covered many times on this channel but I've never been able to answer if a few milliseconds even matter. That's what this video is for. I'm presenting a Rocket League input lag experiment for everyone to participate in, so we can figure out how much accuracy drops with increased input lag, as well as when players start to notice the delay.

There are some challenges that come from the changes that are about to happen. I really hope Psyonix already has plans for all of these issues in place because it could make the game temporarily worse, if they don't.
